.TH "wait_port_offline" 9 "wait_port_offline" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
wait_port_offline \- waits for the specified host FC port go offline
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" wait_port_offline
.BI "(__be64 __iomem *fc_regs "  ","
.BI "u32 delay_us "  ","
.BI "u32 nretry "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fc_regs" 12
Top of MMIO region defined for specified port.
.IP "delay_us" 12
Number of microseconds to delay between reading port status.
.IP "nretry" 12
Number of cycles to retry reading port status.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The provided MMIO region must be mapped prior to call.
.SH "RETURN"
TRUE (1) when the specified port is offline
FALSE (0) when the specified port fails to go offline after timeout
